body_html:
Hi Andrew and thanks for your reply.

I have installed the official WIN package located at https://pypi.python.org/pypi/tensorflow-gpu/0.12.0rc0, following the instructions at https://developers.googleblog.com/2016/11/tensorflow-0-12-adds-support-for-windows.html.

Just to make sure I did not miss anything, I downloaded the .whl file manually, renamed it to .zip, opened and listed all the files and directories inside this package. There is nothing related to android. I am attaching a text file with a list of the files inside the .whl.
I've also checked the Linux package and it also does not contain the Android example.

I guess that these .whl Python distributions do not contain anything other than Python support? If so, I guess that I need another source code/distribution.
Following your advice, I will try the experimental TF Bazel build for Windows and update.

files.txt
